Ambulatory Care Utilization & Chronic Disease Burden Analysis
Executive Summary
Analyzed ambulatory visit patterns and chronic disease burden across multiple health centers to identify high-demand locations, high-need patient groups, and operational pressure points. Insights support better staffing, scheduling, and chronic care program planning.
________________________________________
Business Problem
Leadership lacked a clear view of:
‚Ä¢	Which centers handle the highest volume of visits
‚Ä¢	Where chronic disease patients are concentrated
‚Ä¢	Which patients generate the most chronic-related encounters
Without this visibility, staffing decisions, resource allocation, and patient management programs cannot be targeted effectively.
Goal: Provide data-driven clarity to support operational and clinical decision-making.
